# {{.Type}} ({{.Name}})

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

Notification recipients receive emails about environment lifecycle events from the Microsoft account `no-reply-dynamics365@microsoft.com`. These events include:

- Update availability notifications
- Successful update completions
- Update failures and issues
- Extension validation results
- Environment lifecycle changes

-> **Note:** You can configure up to 100 notification recipients per tenant. For more recipients, use a distribution list email address.

~> **Important:** Ensure notification emails are not filtered to spam folders. Add `no-reply-dynamics365@microsoft.com` to your email allowlist.

## Example Usage

### Basic Notification Recipient

{{tffile "examples/resources/bc_admin_center_notification_recipient/resource.tf"}}

### Multiple Recipients

```terraform
resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "primary_admin" {
  email = "admin@example.com"
  name  = "Primary Administrator"
}

resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "backup_admin" {
  email = "backup-admin@example.com"
  name  = "Backup Administrator"
}

resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "ops_team" {
  email = "ops-team@example.com"
  name  = "Operations Team"
}
```

### Using a Distribution List

```terraform
# For organizations needing more than 100 recipients
resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "bc_admins_list" {
  email = "bc-admins@example.com"
  name  = "Business Central Administrators Distribution List"
}
```

### Partner Notification Setup

```terraform
resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "partner_contact" {
  email = "bc-alerts@partner.com"
  name  = "Partner Support Team"
}

resource "bcadmincenter_notification_recipient" "customer_contact" {
  email = "it-admin@customer.com"
  name  = "Customer IT Administrator"
}
```

